<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="59">
Members of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BED2BB84-3FBC-4BDC-9032-0D537AD3F726" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudolaguvia Misra 1976:253" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudolaguvia</taxonomicName>
are small erethistid catfishes inhabiting hill streams and large rivers in the area bordered by the Ganges River drainage (northern India) to the west and the Sittang River drainage (east-central Myanmar) to the east. The diversity of the group has been doubled in recent years, with eight species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BED2BB84-3FBC-4BDC-9032-0D537AD3F726" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudolaguvia Misra 1976:253" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudolaguvia</taxonomicName>
considered valid (Ng, 2005): 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ribeiroi">P. ribeiroi (Hora, 1921)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shawi">P. shawi (Hora, 1921)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tuberculata">P. tuberculata (Prashad &amp; Mukerji, 1929)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kapuri">P. kapuri (Tilak &amp; Husain, 1975)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4246F4B6-CE44-4B37-85A9-AE3A2E51CBA0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudolaguvia tenebricosa Britz &amp; Ferraris 2003:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenebricosa">P. tenebricosa Britz &amp; Ferraris, 2003</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:43D9CD07-B23E-49B7-A4DD-6CD75DCF5E86" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudolaguvia foveolata Ng 2005:174" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="foveolata">P. foveolata Ng, 2005</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0A75A3D8-3928-42A3-9075-DABC5C68930A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudolaguvia inornata Ng 2005" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inornata">P. inornata Ng, 2005</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9D2F348F-572B-42AF-BB60-8EC94D3534F9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudolaguvia muricata Ng 2005" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricata">P. muricata Ng, 2005</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="59">
A recent collection of fishes in tributaries of the Brahmaputra River drainage in West Bengal, India, included an undescribed 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BED2BB84-3FBC-4BDC-9032-0D537AD3F726" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudolaguvia Misra 1976:253" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudolaguvia</taxonomicName>
species with a terete body that is narrower than congeners. The description of this material as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Pseudolaguvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferula">Pseudolaguvia ferula</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
forms the basis of this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
